personal-knowledge-management","id":"zettel.moc.personal-knowledge-management","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":3,"offset":985},"end":{"line":26,"column":26,"offset":1008},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.202604170003"}],"anchors":{"gagasan":{"type":"header","text":"Gagasan","value":"gagasan","line":14,"column":0,"depth":2},"mengapa-ini-penting":{"type":"header","text":"Mengapa Ini Penting","value":"mengapa-ini-penting","line":24,"column":0,"depth":2},"hubungan-ke-zettel-lain":{"type":"header","text":"Hubungan ke Zettel Lain","value":"hubungan-ke-zettel-lain","line":33,"column":0,"depth":2},"sumber":{"type":"header","text":"Sumber","value":"sumber","line":39,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"zettel","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"koneksi-antar-gagasan-lebih-bernilai-dari-koleksi-informasi\">Koneksi antar gagasan lebih bernilai dari koleksi informasi<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#koneksi-antar-gagasan-lebih-bernilai-dari-koleksi-informasi\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"gagasan\">Gagasan<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#gagasan\"></a></h2>\n<p>Nilai dari sistem pencatatan bukan di <em>berapa banyak</em> yang disimpan, tapi di <em>berapa banyak hubungan</em> yang tercipta antar unit pengetahuan.</p>\n<p>Ini berlawanan dengan intuisi kebanyakan orang. Kita cenderung mengumpulkan: lebih banyak highlight, lebih banyak bookmark, lebih banyak catatan. Tapi koleksi tanpa koneksi hanya menghasilkan <em>kuburan informasi</em>.</p>\n<p>Luhmann menulis: <em>\"It is not important where you place a new note as long as you can link to it.\"</em> Artinya, posisi fisik (atau hierarki folder) tidak penting — yang penting adalah <strong>kemampuan menghubungkan</strong>.</p>\n<p>Insight baru adalah produk dari koneksi yang <em>tidak diharapkan</em>: ketika gagasan dari domain A tiba-tiba relevan dengan masalah di domain B.</p>\n<h2 id=\"mengapa-ini-penting\">Mengapa Ini Penting<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#mengapa-ini-penting\"></a></h2>\n<p>Dalam praktik sehari-hari, ini berarti:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Jangan hanya menyimpan — <strong>hubungkan</strong> setiap Zettel baru ke yang sudah ada</li>\n<li>Saat membuat link, <strong>jelaskan mengapa</strong> link itu dibuat (bukan sekadar taruh link)</li>\n<li>Semakin banyak koneksi yang dibuat dengan <em>sadar</em>, semakin kaya jaring pengetahuanmu</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Ini juga menjelaskan mengapa Wikipedia bukan Zettelkasten — Wikipedia menghubungkan <em>artikel</em>, bukan <em>gagasan</em>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"hubungan-ke-zettel-lain\">Hubungan ke Zettel Lain<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#hubungan-ke-zettel-lain\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Dikuatkan oleh <a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.202604170001\">Second brain memperluas kapasitas berpikir dengan memindahkan beban memori ke sistem eksternal</a> — karena second brain hanya berguna kalau isinya saling terhubung, bukan hanya bertumpuk</li>\n<li>Dikuatkan oleh <a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.202604170002\">Ide yang tidak ditulis sama dengan ide yang tidak ada</a> — karena ide yang tidak ditulis tidak bisa terhubung sama sekali</li>\n<li>Keduanya membentuk dasar dari seluruh praktik Zettelkasten: <strong>tulis → hubungkan → temukan insight baru</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"sumber\">Sumber<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#sumber\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.literature.building-a-second-brain\">Literature Note — Building a Second Brain</a> — Bab 3 tentang \"commonplace book\" dan jaringan ide</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://zettelkasten.de/introduction/\">Introduction to the Zettelkasten Method</a> — bagian \"Connecting Zettel\"</li>\n<li>Niklas Luhmann, <em>Communicating with Slip Boxes</em> (terjemahan)</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"tags\">Tags<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#tags\"></a></h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a class=\"color-tag\" style=\"--tag-color: #a03623;\" href=\"/sotoy/notes/tags.zettel\">zettel</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"color-tag\" style=\"--tag-color: #f0944d;\" href=\"/sotoy/notes/tags.knowledge-management\">knowledge-management</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"color-tag\" style=\"--tag-color: #de9dac;\" href=\"/sotoy/notes/tags.zettelkasten\">zettelkasten</a></li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel\">Zettelkasten</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/notes.zettelkasten\">Zettelkasten di Dendron — Panduan Implementasi</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.202604170001\">Second brain memperluas kapasitas berpikir dengan memindahkan beban memori ke sistem eksternal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.202604170002\">Ide yang tidak ditulis sama dengan ide yang tidak ada</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.literature.building-a-second-brain\">Literature Note — Building a Second Brain</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.moc.personal-knowledge-management\">MOC: Personal Knowledge Management</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"Hello and Welcome! 👋","desc":"","updated":1742030256619,"created":1646842475821,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"453f88f4a5f1ad7629ebb7cc49502125","links":[],"anchors":{"find-more":{"type":"header","text":"Find More","value":"find-more","line":20,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["book-summaries","daily","handbook","notes","tags","til","zettel"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nWelcome to the homepage! I use Dendron to store and organize notes, ideas, and experiments I’m working on. Here are the main sections you’ll find on this site:\n\n1. **Learning Notes** — Practical notes on programming, recent technologies, and productivity tips.\n2. **Personal Projects** — Summaries of projects, experiments, and outcomes I’m working on or have completed.\n3. **Writings & Opinions** — Casual articles and reflections about technology, daily life, and other interesting topics.\n\nI’m constantly experimenting and learning. I hope the content here helps you as a reference, a starting point for discussion, or just light reading.\n\n> Why Dendron?\n>\nDendron helps keep notes organized. Its \"seed\" and \"vault\" concepts make it easy to structure content and find what you need.\n\n## Find More\n\nIf you want to learn more or connect, check these links:\n\n- [Homepage (Dendron)](https://zeihanaulia.github.io/sotoy/)\n- [My GitHub](https://github.com/zeihanaulia)\n- [My Twitter / X](https://x.com/zeihanaulia)\n\nThanks for stopping by. If you have feedback or want to chat, feel free to reach out.\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":true,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart","leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2}},"randomNote":{},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelect":false},"insertNoteIndex":{"enableMarker":false},"copyNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"title"},"templateHierarchy":"template"},"workspace":{"dendronVersion":"0.83.0","vaults":[{"fsPath":"vault"}],"journal":{"dailyDomain":"daily","name":"journal","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd","addBehavior":"childOfDomain"},"scratch":{"name":"scratch","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd.HHmmss","addBehavior":"asOwnDomain"},"task":{"name":"","dateFormat":"","addBehavior":"childOfCurrent","statusSymbols":{"":" ","wip":"w","done":"x","assigned":"a","moved":"m","blocked":"b","delegated":"l","dropped":"d","pending":"y"},"prioritySymbols":{"H":"high","M":"medium","L":"low"},"todoIntegration":false,"createTaskSelectionType":"selection2link","taskCompleteStatus":["done","x"]},"graph":{"zoomSpeed":1,"createStub":false},"enableAutoCreateOnDefinition":false,"enableXVaultWikiLink":false,"enableRemoteVaultInit":true,"enableUserTags":true,"enableHashTags":true,"workspaceVaultSyncMo